title: P0305 (Smart-seq2)
extract_protocol_ch1: Single cells were sorted into 96-well plates (Axygen) chilled to 4°C, prepared with lysis buffer with 1 μl 10 mM dNTP mix (Invitrogen), 1 μl 10 μM Oligo dT primer, 1.9 μl 1% Triton X-100 (Sigma), and 0.1 μl 40 U/μl RNase Inhibitor (Takara). The single cell lysates were sealed and stored frozen at -80°C immediately.
data_processing: The Smart-seq2 data were first processed to filter out low-quality reads when: (1) “N” bases accounting for 10% read length; or (2) bases with quality < 5 account for 50% read length; or (3) containing adapter sequences. The remaining paired-end reads were aligned to the UCSC hg38 human genome reference using kallisto (version 0.43.1) with parameters “--bootstrap-samples=100 --threads=2”. The R package tximport (version 1.9.12) was used to summarize the transcript-level estimated counts into the matrix of gene-level counts.
